# Neither Dockerfile.web nor Dockerfile.api needs any of this from the build
# context — both install/build fresh inside their own stages. Without this
# file, a local `docker build` from the repo root sends the full ~1.2GB
# working tree (node_modules, .venv, .next, .git) to the Docker daemon on
# every build. Production images are unaffected either way (CI builds from a
# fresh checkout with none of this present).
**/node_modules
**/.venv
**/.next
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
.git
.claude
graphify-out
test-results
playwright-report
